modified human granulocyte colony stimulating factor and process to produce the same

Abstract
translated from

A modified human granulocyte-colony stimulating factor (hG-CSF) is produced by culturing a microorganism transformed with an expression vector comprising a gene encoding a modified hG-CSF to produce and secrete the modified hG-CSF to periplasm, said modified hG-CSF being obtained by replacing at least one of the 1st, 2nd, 3rd and 17th amino acids of wild-type hG-CSF (SEQ ID NO: 2) with other amino acid.

Campo da InvenoField of the Invention

A presente inveno refere-se a um fator (hG-CSF) estimulante de colnia de granulcitos humano modificado, um gene codificando o referido peptdeo, um vetor compreendendo o referido gene, um microorganismo transformado com o referido vetor e um processo para produzir o hG-CSF modificado usando referido microorganismo.The present invention relates to a modified human granulocyte colony stimulating factor (hG-CSF), a gene encoding said peptide, a vector comprising said gene, a microorganism transformed with said vector and a process for producing hG -CSF modified using said microorganism.

Antecedentes da InvenoBackground of the Invention

O termo fator estimulante de colnia (CSF) inclui o fator (GM-CSF) estimulante de colnia de granulcitos/macrfagos, fator (M-CSF) estimulante de colnia de macrfagos e fator (G-CSF) estimulante de colnia de granul15 citos, que so produzidos por clulas T, macrfagos, fibroblastos e clulas endoteliais. GM-CSF estimula as clulas indiferenciadas de granulcitos ou macrfagos para induzir a diferenciao das mesmas e proliferao de colnias de granulcitos ou macrfagos. M-CSF e G-CSF primariamente induzem 20 a formao de colnias de macrfagos e granulcitos, respectivamente. In vivo, G-CSF induz a diferenciao de leuccitos da medula ssea e melhora a funo de granulcitos maduros e, conseqentemente, sua importncia clnica no tratamento de leucemia foi bem estabelecida.The term colony stimulating factor (CSF) includes granulocyte / macrophage colony stimulating factor (GM-CSF), macrophage colony stimulating factor (M-CSF) and granulocyte colony stimulating factor (G-CSF) 15 cycles, which are produced by T cells, macrophages, fibroblasts and endothelial cells. GM-CSF stimulates undifferentiated granulocyte or macrophage cells to induce their differentiation and proliferation of granulocyte or macrophage colonies. M-CSF and G-CSF primarily induce the formation of colonies of macrophages and granulocytes, respectively. In vivo, G-CSF induces bone marrow leukocyte differentiation and improves the function of mature granulocytes and, consequently, its clinical importance in the treatment of leukemia has been well established.

Chem. 262, 15208 - 15213 (1987)). A seqncia de aminocidos de hG-CSF consistindo de 174 aminocidos mostrada na fig. 1 e foram realizados muitos estudos para a produo em massa de hG-CSF por manipular um gene codificando referido hG-CSF.Human G-CSF (hG-CSF) is a protein consisting of 174 or 177 amino acids, the 174 amino acid variety having superior neutrophil-enhancing activity (Morishita, K. et al., J. Biol. Chem. 262, 15208 - 15213 (1987)). Neste mtodo de preparao, hG-CSF glicosilado produzido em uma clula de mamferos por emprego de um DNA genmico ou cDNA compreendendo um polinucleotdeo codificando hG-CSF. O hG-CSF glicosilado tem uma cadeia de acar O-glicosdica, 15 mas sabe-se que a referida cadeia de acar no necessria para a atividade de hG-CSF (Lawrence, M. et al. , Science, 232, 61 (1986) ) . Ainda, tambm bem conhecido que a produo de hG-CSF glicosilado empregado em clulas de mamferos requer materiais e instalaes onerosos, e assim, este pro20 cesso no economicamente praticvel.In this method of preparation, glycosylated hG-CSF is produced in a mammalian cell by employing a genomic DNA or cDNA comprising a polynucleotide encoding hG-CSF. The glycosylated hG-CSF has an O-glycosidic sugar chain, 15 but it is known that the said sugar chain is not necessary for hG-CSF activity (Lawrence, M. et al., Science, 232, 61 ( 1986)). In addition, it is also well known that the production of glycosylated hG-CSF employed in mammalian cells requires expensive materials and facilities, and therefore, this process is not economically feasible.

Por volta deste tempo, foram realizadas tentativas para produzir hG-CSF no glicosilado por emprego de um microorganismo, por exemplo, E. coli. In this regard, four of the five Cys residues present in wild-type hG-CSF participate in the formation of disulfide bonds, while the rest contribute to the aggregation of the hG-CSF product during the reduplication process to decrease yield.

Recentemente, a fim de resolver os problemas associados com a produo de uma protena estranha dentro de uma clula microbiana, vrios esforos foram feitos para desenvolver um mtodo baseado em secreo eficiente de uma protena de marcao atravs da membrana da clula microbiana no domnio extra-celular.Recently, in order to solve the problems associated with the production of a foreign protein within a microbial cell, several efforts have been made to develop a method based on efficient secretion of a marker protein through the microbial cell membrane in the extracellular domain .

Os presentes inventores registraram previamente o uso de um novo peptdeo de sinal secretrio preparado por modificao do peptdeo de sinal de E. coli de enterotoxina termo-resistente II (publicao acessvel ao pblico de patente coreana No. 2000 - 19788) na produo de hG-CSF. Especificamente, um vetor de expresso compreendendo um gene hGCSF fixado na extremidade 3' do peptdeo de sinal modificado de enterotoxina II termo-resistente de E. coli foi preparado, e hG-CSF maduro biologicamente ativo, foi expressado por emprego de E. coli transformado com o vetor de expresso. No entanto, a maior parte de hG-CSF expressado acumulou no citoplasma em vez de no periplasma.The present inventors previously registered the use of a new secretory signal peptide prepared by modification of the E. coli signal peptide from thermo-resistant enterotoxin II (publicly accessible publication of Korean patent No. 2000 - 19788) in the production of hG- CSF. Specifically, an expression vector comprising an hGCSF gene fixed at the 3 'end of the E. coli thermoresistant enterotoxin II modified signal peptide was prepared, and biologically active mature hG-CSF was expressed using transformed E. coli with the expression vector. However, the majority of hG-CSF expressed accumulated in the cytoplasm instead of the periplasm.

Os presentes inventores realizaram esforos, com sucesso, para ainda desenvolver um mtodo secretrio eficiente para a produo de hG-CSF em um microorganismo e verificaram que um hG-CSF modificado, que preparado por substituio de pelo menos um resduo de aminocido, especialmente o 17 resduo de cistena, de hG-CSF de tipo selvagem, com outro aminocido, retm a atividade biolgica do tipo selvagem e que o hG-CSF modificado no tendo resduo metionina no N-trmino do mesmo pode ser eficientemente expressado e secretado por um microorganismo quando se emprega um peptdeo de sinal secretrio apropriado.The present inventors have successfully made efforts to further develop an efficient secretory method for the production of hG-CSF in a microorganism and have found that a modified hG-CSF, which is prepared by substituting at least one amino acid residue, especially the 17th cysteine residue, of wild type hG-CSF, with another amino acid, retains the biological activity of the wild type and that the modified hG-CSF without methionine residue at its N-terminus can be efficiently expressed and secreted by a microorganism when an appropriate secretory signal peptide is used.

Quatro dos cinco resduos Cys de hG-CSF participam na formao de ligaes dissulfeto, enquanto o 17 resduo Cys permanece no ligado no estado natural. No entanto, quando uma quantidade grande de hG-CSF expressada em clulas recombinantes, o 17 resduo Cys se torna envolvido na formao de ligao dissulfeto inter-molecular, levando ao acmulo de hG-CSFs aglomerado no citoplasma. No entanto, o hG-CSF modificado inventivo tendo um aminocido diferente de Cys na 17 posio livre deste problema e pode ser efetivamente produzido por um mtodo secretrio usando um microorganismo apropriadamente transformado.Four of the five Cys residues of hG-CSF participate in the formation of disulfide bonds, while the 17th Cys residue remains unbound in the natural state. However, when a large amount of hG-CSF is expressed in recombinant cells, the 17th Cys residue becomes involved in the formation of inter-molecular disulfide bond, leading to the accumulation of clustered hG-CSFs in the cytoplasm. However, the inventive modified hG-CSF having an amino acid other than Cys at 17th position is free of this problem and can be effectively produced by a secretory method using an appropriately transformed microorganism.
